column1: Copied to main database by Kim/Bill

column44: No rain in last 24 hours, wind became light onshore
No rain in last 24 hours, wind became light onshore
VOG and haze, 1 fisherman north of sampling
Peter Martin engaged in conversation about WQ. Wanted to know how cesspools affect WQ.
Team noted that temp on DO probe 0.2 C higher than salinity probe.  This is within tolerance.
Another encounter with Peter Martin asking about water quality data in the Wahikuli region.  Esp nutrient data.
Surfer asked questions about water quality
Lahaina fire 5 days previous of date. Blank pre-sample a little high.
Kayak tour group at site - 4 kayaks in the water and 5 on land about to launch
Light drizzle encountered, lid for bucket used
Salinity at OPM was above 35.0 on second test
Took 4th turbidity reading at OPM since 3rd was greater over 20% difference with the first two readings.
OCO - Did 2nd reading of salinity - value was the same
OUB - Did 2nd reading of salinity - value was 35.9
Had trouble getting D.O probe reading to pop up a few times but eventually it worked
